Abstract: /** * Represents the the dynamic portion of scoping information.  The variableValues are the * values of assigned local or block variables.  The staticScope identifies which sort of * scope this is (block or local). *  * Properties of Dynamic Scopes: * 1. static and dynamic scopes have the same number of names to values * 2. size of variables (and thus names) is determined during parsing.  So those structured do *    not need to change * * FIXME: When creating dynamic scopes we sometimes accidentally pass in extra parents.  This * is harmless (other than wasting memory), but we should not do that.  We can fix this in two * ways: * 1. Fix all callers * 2. Check parent that is passed in and make if new instance is local, then its parent is not local */
